basics.label: Contact Center Specialist
basics.summary: Accomplished and dedicated Customer Service and Administrative professional with over 10 years' experience in the non-profit, finance and healthcare fields. Proven track record of building rapport and establishing lasting relationships with clients and patients. Reliable, trustworthy and driven, with strong time management organizational abilities.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Provided stellar customer service in all aspects of scheduling, including making, canceling, and rescheduling appointments based on appointment guidelines by department. Answered high-volume patient and provider calls (average 90 - 160 calls daily) in a proficient and exemplary manner.
highlights: Attained Top Performer at the GW Medical Faculty Associates status many times in the areas of call volume, attendance and punctuality, call answering time and personal accommodations.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Managed day-to-day operations of Call Center including training staff, management of daily tasks and special projects and department scheduling.
highlights: Exceeded the National Automobile Dealers Association incoming rollover goals by achieving a 55% increase on company assets.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Administered all aspects of NADART plans including preparing, verifying and posting employee and employer contributions, earnings and fees.
highlights: Communicated effectively with Plan Administrators to train on daily processing activities.
